From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Carlos Aguado <caguado@infra.structur.es>
Date: Sun, 27 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: lx2160a-clearfog-cx: add QSFP28/SFP28 EEPROM
 node for transceiver identification

The QSFP28 cage I2C bus (i2c2, 2020000.i2c, Linux i2c-1) exposes the
SFP28 transceiver A0 EEPROM at address 0x50 when a QSFP28-to-SFP28
adapter such as the FS.com MAM1Q00A-QSA28 is installed.

Register the address as an AT24 24c02-compatible EEPROM so the kernel
claims the address and exposes the module identity data (vendor, part
number, serial number, capability flags per SFF-8472) via:

  /sys/bus/i2c/devices/1-0050/eeprom

Note: diagnostic/sensor data (temperature, optical power, bias current)
lives in the SFF-8472 A2 page at 0x51 and is accessible from userspace
via i2c tools (i2cdump -y 1 0x51). Full kernel-managed DOM requires
SFP bus support in the DPAA2 MAC driver, which is not yet implemented.

Signed-off-by: Carlos Aguado <caguado@infra.structur.es>
---
 .../dts/freescale/fsl-lx2160a-clearfog-cx.dts | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-lx2160a-clearfog-cx.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-lx2160a-clearfog-cx.dts
index 848b3c54c351..5ea13938a17e 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-lx2160a-clearfog-cx.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/freescale/fsl-lx2160a-clearfog-cx.dts
@@ -54,6 +54,15 @@ &pcs_mdio6 {
 	status = "okay";
 };

+&i2c2 {
+	/* SFP28 transceiver A0 EEPROM via MAM1Q00A-QSA28 QSFP28-to-SFP28 adapter */
+	qsfp_eeprom: eeprom@50 {
+		compatible = "atmel,24c02";
+		reg = <0x50>;
+		read-only;
+	};
+};
+
 &i2c_smb {
 	/* tx direction */
 	retimer0: retimer@22 {
--
2.43.0

